int ScriptManager::getFuncID ( std::string  moduleName,
std::string  funcName 
)

Get the ID of a function, necesary in order to call script functions with context.

Parameters:
moduleName The name of the module the function is in, in this case it will be the relative path of the file the script is located in.
funcName The name of the function to get the ID of, this only works if there is only one function named funcName in the module (or file in this case).
Returns:
Greater than 0 if the operation succeeeds, less than 0 if no function was found or an error occured.
